&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We partner with leading employers to deliver high-quality, onsite child care that supports working families.and creating opportunities for educators to do what they love (and feel valued while they’re doing it). Join the founding team to support a new employer-sponsored 24-hour onsite child care&amp;nbsp; client center and help build the high-quality program children deserve while pursuing your own professional growth and development.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;As an Assistant Teacher, you will:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Support the Head Teacher in creating a safe, nurturing, and engaging classroom environment&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Assist with implementation of a developmentally appropriate curriculum through play, exploration, and daily routines&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Help maintain compliance with state licensing regulations, health and safety standards, and ratio requirements&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Supervise children and support daily activities including meals, rest time, and transitions&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Build positive relationships with children, families, and team members&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Support classroom organization, cleanliness, and documentation as required&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Step into classroom coverage as needed to maintain proper ratios&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply Today If You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Enjoy working with young children and supporting their growth and development&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Have experience in early childhood education or a related field (preferred but not required, depending on state guidelines)&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Meet or are eligible to meet state requirements for child care staff in a licensed program&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Are willing to complete required background checks and pre-service training in accordance with state regulations&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Demonstrate reliability, teamwork, and a positive attitude&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Have strong communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
