&lt;li&gt;Are committed to health and safety at the highest level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide screen-free care to a variety of children&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have strong technical abilities (responding to emails, text messages, etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are well-versed in child development and best practices (e.g., safe sleep)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are dynamic and creative in their approach to caring for all types of children&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate exceptional oral and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least two years of experience as a nanny or early childhood educator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record of building strong parent partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong references&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with caregiving for a variety of ages ranging from infant through school age&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Vivvi is an equal opportunity employer. Applicants of diverse backgrounds are strongly encouraged to apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
